      <id><![CDATA[OC_SA_R1_INTRO_1]]></id>
      <title><![CDATA[Welcome]]></title>
        <descriptionText><![CDATA[<Introtext style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold; color:#cc0033; margin:10px; padding:0 0 0 5px; background:#e8e8e8; border-bottom:1px solid #333; display:block;">Welcome</Introtext><welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px">Welcome to the <i>OAPI Sales Accelerator Simulation!</i><br>There are four rounds to the simulation, and in each round you will play the role of a Hospital Account Manager with your customer, Maycomb Community Hospital.  Your mentor, “Mack,” will follow you throughout the simulation and provide you with feedback. <br><br>In this first round of the simulation you will use the planning skills you have acquired to identify how to help Maycomb Community Hospital better understand its desired patient treatment goals.<BR><BR>This round of the simulation will include six decisions and should take you 20-30 minutes. Each of the possible questions you consider has been rated according to the following individual metrics, so your score will reflect whether your decision making is in line with these characteristics:<BR><BR><b>Scoring Metrics:</b><BR><span style="color:#3366cc; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; padding-left:20px;">Customer’s Needs</span>
            
            <li style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; color:#333; list-style-type:disc;padding-left:20px;">Decisions will help you better understand your customer's treatment goals for their patients</span></li><li style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; color:#333; list-style-type:disc;padding-left:20px;">Decisions will capture new opportunities for the customer</li><br><span style="color:#3366cc; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold;padding-left:20px;">Sales Progress</span><li style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; color:#333; list-style-type:disc;padding-left:20px;">Decisions build on previous discussions and align with where the customer is in their <span style="margin:0 0 0 16px;">prescribing cycle</span></li><li style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; color:#333; list-style-type:disc;padding-left:20px;">Decisions advance the sale by "closing" at multiple points in the prescribing cycle</li><BR><span style="color:#3366cc; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold;padding-left:20px;">Trusted Advisor Relationship </span><li style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; color:#333; list-style-type:disc;padding-left:20px;">Decisions demonstrate a deep understanding of the customer's priorities and goals</li><li style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; color:#333; list-style-type:disc;padding-left:20px;">Decisions genuinely engage the customer by partnering with the customer to create value</li>
            
            <br></welcomeText><lasttext style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt; color:#000; background-color:#c0c0c0; margin:10px; padding:2px 0 2px 5px; display:block;"><i>Please tap <b>Continue</b> or swipe to see information about you and your customer. </i></lasttext><welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px"><BR><BR><I><B>Simulation Version: January 2012   0711T-3576A</B></I></welcomeText>]]></descriptionText>
